import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.groupby(['symbol']).mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['symbol'], data['price'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c', '#d62728', '#9467bd'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Stock Symbol')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the average price of each stock symbol?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by=['date'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['price'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of stock prices over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of stock prices?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by=['date'])
    data['price_diff'] = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].diff()
    data['volatility'] = data.groupby('symbol')['price_diff'].rolling(30).std().reset_index(0, drop=True)
    data = data.dropna()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    for symbol in data['symbol'].unique():
        symbol_data = data[data['symbol'] == symbol]
        ax.plot(symbol_data['date'], symbol_data['volatility'], label=symbol)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Volatility')
    ax.set_title('What is the volatility of stock prices over time?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
